Class DefaultSource

  • Object
    • AbstractMetadata
      • ModifiableMetadata
        • ISOMetadata
          • DefaultSource
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Emptiable, LenientComparable, IdentifiedObject, Source

    public class DefaultSource
extends ISOMetadata
implements Source
    Information about the source data used in creating the data specified by the scope.
    Relationship between properties
    According ISO 19115, at least one of description and source extents shall be provided.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    Defined in the sis-metadata module

    • Method Detail

      • castOrCopy

        public static DefaultSource castOrCopy(Source object)
        Returns a SIS metadata implementation with the values of the given arbitrary implementation. This method performs the first applicable action in the following choices:
        • If the given object is null, then this method returns null.
        • Otherwise if the given object is already an instance of DefaultSource, then it is returned unchanged.
        • Otherwise a new DefaultSource instance is created using the copy constructor and returned. Note that this is a shallow copy operation, since the other metadata contained in the given object are not recursively copied.
        Parameters:
        object - The object to get as a SIS implementation, or null if none.
        Returns:
        A SIS implementation containing the values of the given object (may be the given object itself), or null if the argument was null.
